-- HSBC Sells 5.6 Million Lira of Discount Uridashi Notes
-- B y   H a r u m i   I c h i k u r a
-- 2012-03-21T16:44:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/hsbc-sells-5-6-million-lira-of-discount-uridashi-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:            HSBC Bank plc
Amount:            5.6 million Turkish Lira
Coupon:            0.50 percent of face value
Issue Price:       64.00 percent of face value
Duration:          7 years
Sales period:      March 22 - April 19
Settlement date:   April 20, 2012
Maturity:          April 18, 2019
Uridashi Manager:  Rakuten Securities Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  